Title: Three Attempts to Replicate the Moral Licensing Effect 
Description: We aim to conduct high-powered replication studies of Study 1 and Study 3 by Sachdeva et al. (2009). 

Citation: Sachdeva, S., Iliev, R., & Medin, D. L. (2009). Sinning saints and saintly sinners: The paradox of moral self-regulation. Psychological Science, 20, 523-528.
Contributors: Irene Blanken, Niels van de Ven, Marcel Zeelenberg, Marijn H. C. Meijers
Tags: Moral balancing, Moral licensing, Moral cleansing

Three Attempts to Replicate the Moral Licensing Effect 
We aim to conduct high-powered replication studies of Study 1 and Study 3 by Sachdeva et al. (2009). 

Citation: Sachdeva, S., Iliev, R., & Medin, D. L. (2009). Sinning saints and saintly sinners: The paradox of moral self-regulation. Psychological Science, 20, 523-528.
